## Market Opportunity

### The Gig Economy Landscape

The global gig economy market was valued at **$582.2 billion in 2025** and is projected to reach **$2.18 trillion by 2034** at a CAGR of 15.79%. Platform-based models provide **40-60% lower operational costs** compared to traditional employment, making them attractive for service businesses.

> Source: [Business Research Insights](https://www.businessresearchinsights.com/market-reports/gig-economy-market-102503)

The handyman and local services platform industry is growing at **13% CAGR** through 2032, with industry revenue estimated at **$14.7 billion by 2030**.

> Source: [Clarro - TaskRabbit Business Model](https://clarro.ca/blog/taskrabbit-handyman-saas-marketplace-business-model/)

### Golf Services Market

**Target Demographics:**
- 47.2 million Americans played golf in 2024
- **80.1% are leisure golfers** (not serious/competitive)
- Average casual golfer plays 15-20 rounds per year
- Premium experiences trending upward
- Corporate entertainment spending remains strong

**Underserved Segment:** Casual golfers who want the "country club experience" without the country club membership or cost. They're willing to pay for unique, memorable experiences.

### Elder Tech Support Market

**Demographics:**
- By 2030, **1 in 6 people globally will be over 60**
- 10,000 Americans turn 65 every day
- Growing "digital divide" as technology advances
- Adult children increasingly burdened with "family IT support"

**Market Pain Points:**
| Problem | Current Solutions | Issues |
|---------|-------------------|--------|
| Mom can't use iPhone | Big box stores | $$$, impersonal, long waits |
| Dad's Wi-Fi is slow | Call ISP | Hours on hold, confusing |
| Grandma got scammed | After-the-fact | No preventive support |
| New device setup | DIY frustration | Wasted family time |

> Source: [Easy Startup Ideas](https://www.easystartupideas.com/p/launch-an-in-home-tech-support-business-for-seniors)

**Real-World Validation:**
> "Richard owns Happy Grandma Senior Tech Support... His inspiration came when his family gifted his grandmother an iPad for Christmas. Her first reaction was 'Take it back!' — she was completely overwhelmed. But over time, he taught her the basics, and she began spending hours on Facebook and YouTube."

> Source: [The Five to Nine Formula](https://www.thefivetonineformula.com/p/tech-support-for-the-elderly)

### Combined Market Opportunity

The genius of Rent-a-Nerd is the **overlapping customer base:**
- Golfers age 45-65 often have elderly parents needing tech help
- Corporate clients buying golf experiences also need tech support
- Gift-givers for both demographics (Father's Day, birthdays)
- Trust established in one service transfers to the other

